		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Hmm...&nbsp; I'll have to duel my necro friends again, but it seemed even with an MR of 200+ I seemed to get 8 out of 10 lifetaps landing on me.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It was annoying for me during those duels because of my limited DD capacity and the fact that my DoTs, while powerfull, aren't as powerfull as the necro's, the battles were long, essentially, it was me dot'ing, nuking, curing myself, cm'ing myself, healing myself, re-snaring/rooting his pet, while the necros would chain LT's, DoT me, CM my dots on them, etc.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Basically we fought each other to a standstill...&nbsp; We were similarly equipped I believe, we seemed to run low on mana at about the same time.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Anyway...&nbsp; For the most part it would seem similarly equip'd druid vs. necro was pretty balanced.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Though I never landed a root or snare on the necro, annoyingly enough...&nbsp; Had I a pet worth a damn I could see where druids might always win (it's annoying that druid's DC pets can be dispelled, but you can't dispell anyone else's pets, but I digress) those battles.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Just thought I'd toss in some anecdotal evidence from a druid vs. necro perspective.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
