			<DIV>My problem with DoT's arent that its landing too often, although it does land pretty often. What i think the problem is, is that when it does land, unless it is cured it does full pvp dmg, each and every time.&nbsp; Furthermore, it can do more than the 40% cap, so u can cast 1 spell and kill someone, especially for them griefers killing naked people.&nbsp; Also, there are 3 classes that can cast DoTs with a curse counter, and since there are no cure curse potions, if one lands on u guess what, it will do the full pvp dmg unless u have a priest with u.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>My suggestion is maybe make it so u can partially resist a dot? or make it so that it can only do so much per tick so that if the DoT plays itself out it can only max at 40%hp? cure curse potions by shammies?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>My problem with rangers is that, even if they fix all the "bugs" like arrow stacking, shooting out the back of their heads while running away, shooting thru buildings, roofs, trees, hills, they can still stay just out of casting range and plug me with arrows with zero risk to themselves, mana free, which is why bow dmg was nerf'd in the first place a&nbsp;year ago right?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Now with wizards, i think they need&nbsp;a small boost, but just that, a small boost, not making them the powerhouse threat that they once were.&nbsp; With 400fr, i still rarely resist a Lure, taking full damage a good 90% of the time. Was watching a wizard test out their lvl 68 big magic nuke with no resist modifier (THundaka i think) and it was landing fine against 500mr, even saw a 3.2 crit.&nbsp; People just have more hp now, so its harder for them to kill, but imo i think their spells land fine.&nbsp; They also have the most trouble killing a priest, but i think everyone has trouble.</DIV>	
