		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Considering that DoTs typically kill slowly enough, especially at the high end of this game, that they can be cured/CM'd, or escape can be made by the person being DoT'd, nerfing them beyond the current PvP nerf of 66% PvE damage seems excessive.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I'm sorry, it's just stupid to try and get a 40% limitation on DoT's just like for DD's when DD's and DoT's function so completely differently in the world of PvP, i.e.:&nbsp; casting a DoT is a long term (relatively speaking for PvP) commitment to battle, a DD however, is not, and considering HT, DT, and MB actually requires more skill to implement.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Let's face it, no where do we see people bitching they were insta-killed by someone's DoT's, where for the past few years, and even currently, you get low enough and a few classes get to press their "I win" button and the fight is over.&nbsp; As opposed to attempting to land a DoT, which has always had to endure a landing resist check, and then has to stay on long enough through cures, CM's, pumice, etc., to do any REAL damage.&nbsp; Plus, as mentioned before, with MOST DoT's, the target will still have a chance to escape the zone and avoid dying a PvP death.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>However, I do agree that each tick of a DoT SHOULD require a resist check in PvP to give everyone a chance of mitigating some of the damage, just like each landing of a DD, or AoE spell requires a seperate resist check, so should each pulse of a DoT.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Prophet Dimento Graven - Level 70 <br>Echo of Destruction<br>www.fodpovar.com<br><br>Self Appointed EQ Curmudgeon
