		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>that is probably because you are a crappy necro. Sorry had to point it out because you obviously dont use your class abilities to their full potential.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>First and foremost, you faced against a Paladin and couldnt kill him? **SMURF**, nerf paladins because surely a necro should be able to kill a paladin pretty much always, same with cleric too. God forbid there is a class that necromancer cannot kill just by chaining lifetaps.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>#1. Your claim that&nbsp;resist adjusted&nbsp;lifetaps will be useless is a lie or sign that you do not know how to play your own class. They will no longer will be the BEST DD AVAILABLE IN GAME to a NECRO that shouldnt have best DD to begin with, but by no means it will be useless. They can still be used as means of self healing (by tapping eye or a low lvl monster). Back when resists were at their normal stage (pre -400) necromancers actually used lifetaps to HEAL themselves, not just to nuke people down a la wizard.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>#2. Class defining ability of necromancer was always dots. May be you missed the memo, but its always been the DOTS that made necromancers a CLASS. I am sorry if your idea of pvp consists of standing still and nuking anyone down tapping hps back. That is NOT what a pure caster should be able to do in pvp. EVER. Necromancers have HoT dot and wide range of other dots that are anywhere from extremely dangerous to absolutely deadly. May be if you didnt just nuke people toe to toe but /cough /cough learned to PvP on your own class, you wouldnt have this "problem".</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>#3. Necromancers are overpowered even without the lifetap. The unresitable, un-interruptable lifetap that is better in PvP than a lure is UN BALANCING. Do you see what SoE did to SKs? That happened because SKs were UN BALANCED. If you dont agree to balancing of necromancers, evil boogeyma.. err SoE will balance your class in manner in which SKs were balanced. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Now back to Mearis.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>#1. Pets are healable and UN killable if you summon/suspend them. Thus if you dont just stand there and take attack from FRONT, note FRONT, but actually have pet CHASING people, interrupting their CASTING and uh oh dealing damage from.. read this "BACK" and not against best geared warrior on server, but say a /cough less geared people, a lvl 65 pet is DPS enough.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>#2. Guess what, a mage pet shouldn't be able to SOLO a lvl 65 cleric. That would be a sign of what we, the pvpers, call an "IMBALANCE". When a pet that you make is supposed to be capable of "COUGH" killing a lvl 65 cleric or running him OOM and then killing, that is a sign that there is something WRONG with a game.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Here, do this for your test mearis. Fully buff pet (that means FoS, Virtue, BSS, Haste) arm it with weapons, DS it and send a rogue 1 on 1 against it meleeing. I want to see who dies first.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Mage pets along with necro pets and bst pets are perfectly balanced in PvP if not overpowered via the "pet affinity AA" that once again introduces seloed pets that can attack people in the middle of 20 mobs while the mage is sitting at zone in.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I can name you so many situations where mage pet is rediculously overpowered, but you know them all yourself. So /shrug.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Quikc recap:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1. Sitizen is a nuke happy necro that needs to learn how to play his class before speaking on these boards regarding class balance.</DIV>
<DIV>2. Mearis should stop asking for a better pet, a better nuke, a nerf of all other classes vs a mage and etc.</DIV>
<DIV>3. MiM sucks</DIV>	
