		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Again Sadko, you are twisting facts to suit your own interpretation of things.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Yes, pets with selos are very good at interrupting casters.&nbsp; That is because SELO is extremly powerful as a PvP tool (I don't need to explain that to you) but you cannot assume that for balance a mage is always grouped with a bard.&nbsp; All classes grouped in PvP with a bard are much more deadly, that's the proper nature of the class.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>You merely bring up example where either a class weakness (rogues to damage shield) or having the best support class along makes a class shine.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>For example, a warrior fighting against a druid will get caned horribly.&nbsp; A warrior with a bard giving him selos and keeping him PoV'd will destroy that druid if he is any competent at jousting.&nbsp; That doesn't mean that warriors are super powerful versus PvP gods, merely that bards enhance all classes they are with.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Listen, I am not in any way shape or form arguing for the return of overpowered pets in PvP, like Epic in the hands of low 50s gankers.&nbsp; That is a horrible imbalance, and if a way can be found to fix it, it should be.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I am merely suggesting that a fully buffed pet, with every single pet related AA, with full gear, attacking a target that doesn't fight back with only a 20 point damage shield, should be able to do more than 17% damage before dying.&nbsp; If the warrior would turn his attention to the pet, I believe the warrior should easily dispatch it, but I do not believe that the current status is balanced, since mages are a very significant portion of mage damage.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Second, about 'it' screwing up balance versus mages and wizards.&nbsp; Realistically speaking, alll a wizard has to do to defeat a mage is use a temp flux staff to 'overwrite' calliav &amp; prism skin, then pop the pet in either one nuke or two crits, then it comes down to a mage without a pet vs a wizard.&nbsp; A pet with a higher DPS will still be a non issue versus most good wizards.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>About 'suspending' pet to keep it immortal.&nbsp; Suspended minion takes 3 second to cast, has 100 range, and requires the pet is not aggro'd onto any mob, nor any mob aggro'd onto pet.&nbsp; It then takes 3 more seconds to unsuspend.&nbsp; It does NOT become insta healed the moment it is unsuspended, and frankly its most useful use is if you are trying to sneak invis and need to carry a pet with you.&nbsp; One usually doesn't have the time to suspend/unsuspend pet in the heat of a battle, since it gains nothing useful.</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
